### Interpretation (ties to 07-RESEARCH.md Pitfall 2 / Open Question 1)

Per research, detekt 1.23.8's Gradle-9 incompatibility CANNOT be empirically
observed on Gradle 8.11.1 — detekt applies Kotlin/AGP as compileOnly, so its
Gradle-8.x-targeted internal API usage does not trip the deprecation reporter
until the build actually runs on Gradle 9 (which requires AGP 9 — Phase 8).
This enumeration therefore establishes the CURRENT (Gradle 8.11.1) deprecation
surface = EMPTY. The detekt-on-Gradle-9 empirical test is deferred to Phase 8's
first green-on-Gradle-9 build, exactly as the research recommends. The recorded
decision intent stands: keep detekt 1.23.8, accept/track its Gradle-9 warnings if
they appear in Phase 8, do NOT pre-emptively adopt the 2.0.0-alpha line.

